beautiful little place much better than the photos, has great parking in front of the house , east to get onto the highway to get around from the house,

This space is incredible. It's extremely clean, organized, quiet, private, and spacious. It's very comfortable and inviting. I quickly felt as if I was at home. What is more, Cory and Vanessa are responsive hosts. I will be sure to return. Thank you!

great, cozy little place. would happily stay again. thank you!

Carrie’s place is cozy, beautifully decorated and incredibly thoughtfully laid out. Snacks and refreshments and a beautiful view were an added bonus. Carrie was friendly, and very responsive. Highly recommend her place.

Wow! Was my first impression with Carries Air bnb. One of the best Air bnb’s I have rented. Carrie is very kind and thoughtful. The property had many extras! Cozy, clean & comfortable. 😊😊😊

This was my second stay at Carrie's place for a week. The apartment is very clean, well-furnished, and full of the amenities you need for a longer stay. I felt right at home there. My partner and I absolutely loved our stay at Karolina’s loft! It was very welcoming, and offered a great night view of the Calgary Tower.

Absolutely loved our stay, the loft was spotless, cosy, and location was great. Karolina was great with communication and made sure we had everything we needed. Wish we could have spent more time here.
Enjoyed! Great place for my few nights in Calgary.

Bridgeland is a great quaint part of Calgary..

My partner and I stayed in Karolina‘s beautiful suite for just a night but it was an amazing experience! The suite looks very new and stylishly furnished. The place was very clean and looked as amazing as on the pictures. Close to the suite is a nice cafe for breakfast and a small supermarket. 
Thanks to Karolina for a wonderful stay!

We had a great stay at Karolina’s place. It was spotless, comfortable and the big windows give the place a nice ambience. Would stay here again in a heartbeat.

One of the best Airbnb stays we’ve ever had! My partner and I thoroughly enjoyed our time here. On top of that, Karolina and her husband were outstanding hosts - genuinely friendly, thoughtful, and incredibly responsive. I highly recommend this place to anyone wanting a true Calgary experience!
It was a very nice place to stay! Thanks!

 It was very hot inside the suite when we arrived (no AC during a bit of a heatwave), but I messaged the host late at night about it and they had a brand new fan ready for us by following morning which was hugely appreciated. We also left a necklace at the suite and the host had it mailed to us. Very grateful for their responsiveness! Exceeded our expectations in that respect. 

The location was ok, walkable (25 min) to downtown. Some cafes and a couple bars nearby. Overall it was very expensive (stampede pricing!), but a good experience.

Karolina was a great host and we enjoyed staying at her property. The property is exactly as described and pictured in the app, in very good condition and very well maintained. Karolina was always responsive and willing to help us, both with our stay and to enjoy our time in Calgary as well. The location of this place is also a wonderful neighborhood, with really nice bars, cafes, local restaurants and delicious ice cream all just 2-3 blocks from Karolina’s property. It was a great experience and we’d happily stay there again on our next return to Calgary!

Madeline’s place was a great location for a weekend stay in Calgary. Lots of local attractions nearby and a very walkable community. The environment is clean, and the furniture and household items are well-equipped. The surrounding area is also very quiet. However, transportation is not very convenient, as both buses and trains require a bit of walking.
Madeline’s place is in a convenient location, a quiet, friendly neighbourhood. Around 15 minutes walk to the shops at Bridgeland and the C train.

Good place

One of the most thoughtfully laid out Airbnbs I have ever stayed at, in the most lovely, centrally located, walkable neighbourhood. Easy check-in and checkout, and spotlessly clean. I will definitely be back; thank you for the perfect stay!

We thoroughly enjoyed our stay and will try to stay there the next time we come to Calgary!

Stayed here while I was in Calgary for work. The loft had a great location with plenty of restaurants nearby, a generally safe area, and convenient features like a yoga studio across the street. It was clean and modern, with a lovely overhead shower, a new kitchen, and a cute shop, ‘Tuu,’ downstairs. Have a parking space was great too.

However, there were some privacy concerns. The host attached an AirTag to the keys, which tracked my location and sent notifications to my iPhone (and coworkers iPhones at work), making me feel monitored. Additionally, a camera by the front door records your comings and goings. Noise from people walking upstairs every morning also made it hard to sleep since the bed is so close to the ceiling.

While the price and location were great, the constant feeling of being tracked detracted from the stay. Great for some, but privacy-conscious travelers may want to think twice.

We had a great time at Mike's place!

Pros:
- Beautiful apartment
- very clean
- the rainshower was exquisite
- it's location is great for walking to restaurants and stores
- secure building
- parking space
- Mike was very responsive

Cons:
- The building is right beside a train track, and the sound of the trains are loud enough to get through the walls. We were woken up every night from the trains
- The bed situation leaves something to be desired. You have to kind of crawl on your hands and knees to get into the bed. There's also no place for side tables. As someone who drinks water throughout the night, I had to shove my water bottle between the mattress and the railing
- The breakers seem a tad... weak? The breaker for the oven had been tripped when we arrived, and using a hair dryer tripped the breaker for the bathroom

Overall, we had a great time here! Just consider the bed situation if you have any knee issues or other physical ailments.

My husband & I and our 2 cowboy corgi dogs stayed at Tiffany's for 2 nights & 3 days this winter. Things that stood out were Tiffany's up front & friendly communication, coordinating to allow us an early check in, plus so much attention to detail in the space. Luxurious sheets, pillows, comfy beds, comfy couches, delightful bath products from Rocky Mountain Soap Co, lots of cozy blankets, dog bowls for our pups, and our favourite was the welcome gift of 2 incredibly delicious donuts from a nearby local bakery that were left to welcome us at Check In. We had such a comfortable and welcoming stay, plus the area was so nice with all the loveliest restaurants you could desire- also so vegan friendly which was a huge plus! Highly recommend for a pampered stay to unwind & enjoy Calgary. Would absolutely stay again!

This is our second time staying at Tiffany’s and I wish I could gatekeep this place (but I won’t!) It’s the perfect home base for my family whenever we’re in Calgary - close to the zoo, Telus Spark + all the shops/neighbourhood of Inglewood. Tiffany is the best host and we look forward to staying here again soon!

Wow! Tiffany’s laneway home is the full package! It’s quiet and private. The south facing windows allow the incredible sun to shine in. At the east window you feel like you are in a tree house. The beds are super comfortable and the legs of the bedframe are wrapped so you don’t stub your toes. Just one example of how Tiffany is attentive to the details. The sheets, towels and toiletries are luxurious. The kitchen is super well equipped. The laundry machines are efficient (no waiting around for the usual apartment style dryer to take 2 hours). Having the ability to adjust the thermostat is great. Parking was easy and Tiffany made sure our vehicle was registered before we arrived. Note if you are coming with a dog, there was a dog next door who became overly excited (barking paws up on the fence) when we passed by with our dog. If your dog is reactive or nervous, they may become overwhelmed. Tiffany is super clear and friendly in her communication. Book it!

The suite is new, well equipped, bright, and comfortable. It is well suited for long term stays. The location makes it almost effortless to explore what Calgary has to offer. If you want to go downtown, find a restaurant, or hit up a fitness centre, they are all close by. If you want to get across or out of of the city, the big highways are close by too. 

The only downside that is worth mentioning is the proximity to railroad tracks. There is a considerable amount of train traffic with the usual rumbling, dinging, and screeching that cargo trains make. While not a constant, you can expect it any time of day or night. If your brain filters out these sort of urban sounds, then you will likely be happy and comfortable here.

Super great place, very close to everything you need. The bed was very comfortable, as well as the sofa. The place was very clean and well decorated. Christal was great and checked in on us half way through our stay to see if we needed anything. We will definitely be returning.

Overall had an excellent stay at his place! Nicely renovated basement suite in a good area of town. Jayden was very responsive to questions and felt us feel at home!

Better than perfect for our stay. It has a lovely welcoming mellow mood that's refreshing after a hectic day. Host is super responsive and helpful. Heather was responsive right away,  easy to comminuted with and ask any questions.  Easy to get in upon arrival,  very clean and comfortable welcoming feeling when u enter place.  Would highly recommend to stay.  Would stay again for sure!!

PS: the bed in the bedroom is a double, so sleeping may be a little close (there is a 2nd bed in an alcove off the living room).

The beds are fulls not queens and the duvet had yellow stain marks as well as bed frames were very creaky. Just a heads up to folks about the check in process to make it a little clearer.

There is a touchscreen which is used to enter a dial code, which will ring the hosts cell phone. The touchscreen doesn’t default to code enter screen, you have to hit the ‘CODE #’ button in the top right of the screen. 
Once you enter the provided code it will dial the hosts phone number, they will then push a button on their phone to open both of the front door AND will ‘unlock’ the elevator access to the floor.
If you follow someone through the door without the host ‘buzzing’ you in, you won’t be able to use the elevator to get to your floor.

**This is only required for your very first check in.**

Once you have the fob, you’re good to go.

Once checked in, we experienced consistent beeping (24 hours a day, for the entire stay) from the fire alarm panel located directly outside the unit door. There was louder, more disruptive fire alarm testing happening for the week we were there - which the host was apparently unaware of (even though a notice was posted in the elevator, dated 15 days prior to our arrival). Our host repeatedly promised compensation for the disruption, but eventually stopped responding altogether. Even now, the last message I have from them says they're 'investigating'. 
I'd strongly recommend booking elsewhere - if anything goes wrong with your stay, you'll need to escalate to AirBnb directly because in our experience, attempting to work directly with the host is useless.

Inside, there are a handful of steps to go up and then there’s an elevator. It didn’t look like there was an option around the steps for people with mobility barriers.

everything was perfect. location, communication from host, beautifully clean, all amenities great., including coffee machine, full kitchen. Also the luxury of a laundry room. Very quiet and beautiful spot on the top of the hill. Would love to stay again.

It was in easy walking distance to downtown and prince’s island park. The gate at the front was a bit tricky to open but if you push it forward slightly and lift the latch it opens towards you with ease. Also some great views of city.
i had really good time

We had a wonderful stay! The place was clean and conveniently close to the city, which was a huge plus. We stayed on the lower level, which was a bit smaller than expected, but the location was fantastic. The neighborhood was peaceful, and the place was fully stocked with everything we needed. We highly recommend this place to others and would definitely come here again!
the team was very helpful.

very accommodating and the location is second to none.  
cute little home away from home.

Amy was attentive to us at all times, the apartment had everything she said except that it was very dirty when we arrived, the terrace was unusable, the kitchen table was covered in dust, and some furniture was in very bad condition. The heating is a bit old and if it doesn't work by lowering the temperature it is best to turn it off, we spent a long time struggling with that. Regarding the rest, it is well located and the neighborhood is quiet, you just have to be careful with the homeless.

The place was nice for the price. Additionally, Amy’s response time was quick and was very professional! I just wish there were pictures or a list of the kitchen utensils because I ended bringing the same tools that were there…even though she said she didn’t have them. Moreover,  I stayed during the winter season so it was really cold due to the amount of windows leaking cold air and the marble floors even with the heat turned up… so bring warm clothes with you! However, the apartment was clean and the pictures matched the place. There were also lots of yummy places to eat nearby. Overall, it was a good experience :)

The place is easy to find and check-in process was easy. Amy was a responsive host and easy to communicate with.

The building is located in downtown Calgary, very convenient and is close to the Bow River. The unit we lived in has a nice river view. However, it could use better maintenance. When we first moved in, four out of the five lights in the kitchen were not working, but Amy had someone come to fix them the next day. The showerhead in the bathroom leaks water from the faucet below, the sink doesn’t have a stopper, the blinds in the bedroom is not working properly, the switch for the bedside light is broken, and there’s only one towel rack in the bathroom, which is loose and almost falling off..... We have already informed the host about these issues, so hopfully it'll be corrected soon. 

All things considered, based on the location and cost, it’s still worth staying here.

Amy’s place was a great place to sleep for the night between our flights 
Keep in mind she does ask that you check in before 11pm 
Our flight landed at 1030 but she was still very nice and sent us clear instructions to get in afterwards. 
That was my fault.
Great place to stay at.
Great clean place in a good location. Easy check in and clear instructions.

This is a great place for the price you pay and conveniently located near many popular spots. However, if you plan to cook more than you order takeout, be aware that there is no frying pan (just sauce pans) or basic cooking/pantry staples, so you’ll need to bring your own.
Great stay, minutes walking distance from downtown Calgary. Amy was super easy to communicate with, easy check-in and check-out as well.
Great for two people especially in the heart of downtown. the view id also great.

Excellent place. Great location, rooms were spotless, and host was gracious enough to allow an early check in.
